President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Charles P. Blahous III as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Social Security Trust Funds. Dr. Blahous is currently a Research Program Director and Senior Research Fellow at the Mercatus Center at George Mason University and a Research Fellow at the Hoover Institution at Stanford University. He previously served as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Social Security Trust Funds from 2010 to 2015. Dr. Blahous has also worked in various positions in government, including as Deputy Director of the National Economic Council under President George W. Bush and as a Special Assistant to the President for Economic Policy. He has a background in chemistry and received his Ph.D. in Computational Quantum Chemistry from the University of California, Berkeley.